verse.lines:
{lang-eng}I’ve found the one of peerless worth;
My heart now sings for joy;
And sing I must, for Christ I have;
Oh, what a Christ have I!{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}My Christ, He is the Lamb of God,
Who full salvation brings;
He is the Sun of Righteousness,
With healing in His wings.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}My Christ, He is the Tree of Life
With fruit abundant, sweet.
My hunger He does satisfy;
Of Him I daily eat.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Christ is my captain and my guard,
My teacher and my guide,
My bridegroom, master and my head;
In me He does reside.{/lang-eng}
